
[1]puddening

   PUD'DENING, n. In seamen's language, a thick wreath or circle of
   cordage, tapering from the middle towards the ends, and fastened about
   the mast below the trusses, to prevent the yards from falling down when
   the ropes sustaining them are shot away.
